Key Interview Questions:
Addressing common DevOps interview questions:
What is DevOps?
Why is DevOps used?
How to introduce oneself for a DevOps position.
Description of day-to-day activities as a DevOps engineer.

Definition and Goals of DevOps:
DevOps aims to improve the organizational ability to deliver applications efficiently.
Emphasis on automation, quality, monitoring (observability), and testing.
DevOps is not just about CI/CD but encompasses continuous improvement in delivery processes.

Evolution and Role of DevOps:
Historical context: Before DevOps, multiple roles (system admins, build and release engineers) were involved in the delivery process.
DevOps merges these roles into a single team to streamline and expedite application delivery.
